data.title: British Comedies from the 1950s
meta_keywords: Year Years Decades Time Broadcast Dates Guide Information 1950s
data.meta_description: A list of British comedies that launched between 1959 and 1950.
data.text:
1959

New titles in 1959 included The Navy Lark, Too Many Crooks, Alive And Kicking, Stick 'Em Up, The Ugly Duckling, Carry On Teacher, Don't Panic, Chaps!, Left, Right And Centre, Make Mine A Million and Life Is A Circus.

1958

New titles in 1958 included Bachelor Of Hearts, The Square Peg, Beyond Our Ken, Davy, Carry On Sergeant, The Duke Wore Jeans, Law And Disorder, The Big Money, The Larkins and Next To No Time!.

1957

New titles in 1957 included Brothers In Law, Barnacle Bill, Blue Murder At St. Trinian's, The Army Game, Carry On Admiral, The Passionate Stranger, The Clitheroe Kid, Just My Luck, The Naked Truth and The Truth About Women.

1956

New titles in 1956 included A Touch Of The Sun, It's Great To Be Young!, Jumping For Joy, Before Your Very Eyes, The March Hare, Keep It Clean, You Lucky People!, It's A Wonderful World, Fun At St. Fanny's and It's A Great Day.

1955

New titles in 1955 included Make Me An Offer!, Miss Tulip Stays The Night, The Benny Hill Show, Sunday Night At The London Palladium, Doctor At Sea, That's An Order, An Alligator Named Daisy, All In Good Fun, Oh... Rosalinda!! and To Paris With Love.

1954

New titles in 1954 included Orders Are Orders, The Crowded Day, The Gay Dog, The Love Lottery, What Every Woman Wants, For Better, For Worse, Happy Ever After, Calling All Cars, The Million Pound Note and The Final Test.

1953

New titles in 1953 included Is Your Honeymoon Really Necessary?, Meet Mister Lucifer, Forces' Sweetheart, There Was A Young Lady, Trouble In Store, Those People Next Door, Our Girl Friday, Will Any Gentleman...?, Isn't Life Wonderful and The Captain's Paradise.

1952

New titles in 1952 included The Pickwick Papers, Song Of Paris, Time Gentlemen Please!, Curtain Up, You're Only Young Twice!, Meet Me Tonight, Treasure Hunt, Miss Robin Hood, Girdle Of Gold and Father's Doing Fine.

1951

New titles in 1951 included The Lavender Hill Mob, Traveller's Joy, Appointment With Venus, The Man In The White Suit, Let's Go Crazy, Penny Points To Paradise, The Goon Show, Madame Louise, The Kilties Are Coming and Happy Go Lovely.

1950

New titles in 1950 included A Ray Of Sunshine, The Girl Who Couldn't Quite, Life With The Lyons, Educating Archie, Over The Garden Wall, Something In The City, Old Mother Riley, Headmistress, The Happiest Days Of Your Life, Chance Of A Lifetime and Last Holiday.
